<h3>LT booking</h3>
<p>
  If it is found that a specific fixed asset is useless, the Plant Manager or the Department Manager who is a user
  of said fixed asset makes a proposal to liquidate it.
</p>
<p>
  Liquidation of a fixed asset may take place through the sale of an obsolete asset,
  physical liquidation i.e. scrapping - LT, and partial liquidation of a fixed asset.
</p>
<p>
  In each case, the basis for further actions is a protocol of redundancy of the fixed asset,
  signed by the user, approved by the committee, and the Management Board of the Company.
  The approved document is sent to Infosys for verification.
</p>
<p>
  Infosys supplements the fiscal and economic values, and the redemption of the asset and then sends
  the document to the approval of the owner of the asset.
</p>
<p>
  If the owner has no objections, he accepts the verified LT document, which is sent to Pune for posting.
</p>
